AIf you're following live, you've noticed that space robots move verrry slooowly. For good reason, too. Safety first! Always!
#Dextre was developed to reduce the need for astronauts to conduct spacewalks for routine maintenance on the #ISS's exterior.
Before #Dextre started replacing RPCMs in 2010, exchanging the boxes was done by spacewalkers, which always carries a certain level of risk.
RPCMs control the flow of electricity through the #ISS’s secondary power distribution system, and tend to fail over time.
#Dextre is removing circuit breaker boxes, aka by their technical name: “Remote Power Control Modules (RPCMs).
